name: Viva Goa Restaurant Colva

reviews.review_text: Landed up after looking at google reviews, One hell of a place for food, Friendly owners, Awesome food, Service is excellent. Definitely gijng to recommend.

Rajesh Singh was great host. Enjoyed all dishes. Seafood , chicken and cocktails all were good. Quite place . Landed with google reviews but turned up to be good decision. Will be in list whenever travel this side.

I spent two months in the Colva/Benaulim area and visited Viva Goa many times. The food and service were consistently good, genuine Goan flavours. Of all the restaurants in the immediate area I would choose this one to go to. The only caveat is that they do offer a karaoke mike to customers on the weekend, karaoke is one of my pet hates, so if you're like me I'd avoid it on Friday & Saturday nights. Otherwise, recommended for good food & service.

description:
**Viva Goa Restaurant: A Culinary Gem in Colva, Goa**

With an impressive rating of 4.4 out of 5 based on 1,656 reviews, Viva Goa Restaurant in Colva, Goa, has quickly established itself as a must-visit destination for both locals and tourists seeking authentic Goan flavors. Praised for its seafood offerings (47 mentions), delectable fish curry (17 mentions), pleasant atmosphere for trips (16 mentions), and musical ambience (14 mentions), this restaurant clearly captures the heart of Goan culinary culture.

**Ambiance & Design**

Viva Goa Restaurant welcomes diners with an inviting and cheerful ambiance. The décor is charmingly rustic, adorned with traditional Goan elements that create a cozy yet lively atmosphere. In several customer-provided images, you can see cozy wooden furniture paired with vibrant wall art that reflects the spirit of Goa. Natural light pours in through open spaces, enhancing the laid-back vibe. While the restaurant thrives on its appeal as a tranquil spot to unwind with good food, guests have pointed out that the weekend karaoke can make for a more animated experience—something to consider for those easily distracted by music.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at Viva Goa is a celebration of Goan cuisine, with a strong focus on seafood. Signature dishes, particularly the seafood platter and fish curry, consistently receive high praise from patrons. Reviewers rave about the genuine Goan flavors that the restaurant embodies. One guest noted their frequent visits, emphasizing the consistently high standard of food and service. Beautifully presented, every dish not only tantalizes the taste buds but is a feast for the eyes—something showcased effectively in the collection of food photos, where vibrant colors and careful plating catch attention.

Viva Goa also caters to a variety of dietary preferences, accommodating chicken lovers, seafood aficionados, and cocktail enthusiasts alike—making it a versatile choice for any group.

**Customer Experience & Service**

The positive sentiments extend beyond just the food; customers highlight the warm and attentive service provided by the staff. Rajesh Singh, identified as a great host, has been mentioned in a review noting how he enhances the dining experience through his friendly demeanor. The outstanding service makes for a welcoming vibe, ensuring that diners feel at home. Reservations aren’t explicitly mentioned, making it a good casual spot for walk-ins, although arriving early on weekends may provide a quieter dining experience before the karaoke fun kicks in.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Viva Goa has quickly garnered a loyal customer base, bolstered by its active presence on social media platforms. The buzz generated through customer reviews, many of which mirror the lively dining experience, speaks volumes about the restaurant's reputation. A sense of community is palpable, as many reviews mention returning visits and recommendations to friends. The acknowledgment of karaoke on weekends adds an element of fun, appealing to younger crowds and those looking for a festive evening.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The stunning array of customer-provided images showcases the enchanting interior and the beautifully presented dishes. From vibrant fish thalis to colorful cocktails, each photograph is a testament to the culinary artistry at play. The ambiance photos encapsulate the inviting atmosphere, making potential visitors feel the warmth and friendly ambiance before they even step inside.

In summary, Viva Goa Restaurant in Colva is not just a place to eat; it is an experience steeped in rich flavors, great service, and a strong sense of community that captures the essence of Goa. Whether you are a seafood lover or simply in search of hearty Goan cuisine, a visit here promises to be memorable.
